    <td class="roweven" valign="top" width="2000">New Features<br>------------<br>- Updated documentation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Added a troubleshooting section (Zsolt Botykai).<br>- Updated outlookvim.js to display a message if double clicked on to determine if Windows Script Host is correctly installed.<br>- Updated outlookvim.bas (the Outlook VBScript Macro) to show an error if it cannot access the file system.&nbsp;&nbsp;Modified all the message boxes Outlook may display to indicate &quot;OutlookVim:&quot; is displaying the message.<br>- You can specify whether new emails should be opened in a new tab via the g:outlook_use_tabs configuration option (Zsolt Botykai).<br><br>After unzipping the contents into your vimfiles directory, copy and paste the outlookvim.bas file into your Outlook macro created earlier (ALT-F11 in Outlook).<br><br>Also from within Vim run (choose the location where the plugin was installed):<br>:helptags $VIM\vimfiles\doc</td>
</tr>
